title: Colts gets past Jaguars in overtime
text:
Colts gets past Jaguars in overtime 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive Indianapolis Colts October 4, 2015 Updated Oct 4, 2015 at 9:59 PM EDT 
INDIANAPOLIS, Ind. (21 Alive) - Adam Vinatieri booted a 27 yards field goal in overtime Sunday to give the Colts a 16-13 win over the Jacksonville Jaguars and the lead in the AFC South Division. 
Matt Hasselback, playing in place of the injured Andrew Luck, threw for 282 yards and a touchdown, but it was Vinatieri doing most of the scoring with his three field goals on the way to becoming the team franchise all time scoring leader. 
Jacksonville kicker Jason Myers missed two field goal tries at the end of regulation that would have given the Jags the win, and then another in overtime   To submit a comment on this article, your email address is required.
